Legislators will question the Council of Governors, university managements and commissions that have not adhered to the 30 per cent ethnic threshold in hiring staff.The Committee on National Cohesion and Equal Opportunity yesterday resolved to summon top management of public institutions that haven t met the ethnic representation threshold.On Monday, the National Cohesion and Integration Commission released a report saying that in many institutions, some tribes were more than 30 per cent of the staff. Chairman Francis Kaparo told the committee that the Judicial Service Commission is the worst among 15 commissions, with 39 per cent of its staff from the Kikuyu community.He said Parliament should compel institutions to acquire NCIC clearance certificates to ensure equity in hiring. NCIC should be empowered to vet recruitment processes before letters of appointment are issued, Kaparo said.